Based on historical data , the average rate of return for small-company stocks is $16.6\%$ with a standard deviation of $31.9\%$.

We can then use the formula for the Z-score to solve for the probability:

$$\begin{aligned}
Z&=\dfrac{X-\text{Average return}}{\text{Standard deviation}}
\end{aligned}$$

Where X is the desired value.
